; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/sha256.fk form-stdlib/decidable-channel.fk
;
; decidable-channel-band — STONE 46. Twelve claims about a channel on which
; silence is impossible. Verdict 4095 when every one crosses.
;
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; APORON — THE DECLARED RADIUS. Read this before believing the number.
;
; WHAT THIS BAND PROVES
;   * That an ack of `nothing` and an ack never sent are DIFFERENT NUMBERS from the same total
;     function — 0 and -1 — and that neither answer required waiting for anything. This is the
;     stone; claim 16 is where it lands and claim 512 is where its edges are walked.
;   * That a frame cut at ANY byte position is refused, and specifically that a cut whose remaining
;     bytes are THEMSELVES a valid shorter message is still refused. The concrete pair is the one
;     that cost this session real time: `(do (add 1 2))` cut to `(do (add 1 2)`, where the cut text
;     is a strict byte PREFIX of the whole and parses cleanly on its own.
;   * That resolution is independent of order, over SIX named orderings including one in which
;     every reply precedes every question and one containing duplicates.
;   * That the one thing which WOULD have made order matter — two acks disagreeing about the same
;     offer — is refused by name (CONFLICT) rather than settled by position.
;   * That bytes which never crossed the frame interface are counted as breach rather than skipped.
;   * That a close carries its reason and the digest it closed on, and that a close, a plain stop,
;     and a cut are three different numbers.
;
; WHAT IT DOES NOT PROVE
;   * NOT that the transport is reliable. There is no transport here at all. Every transcript in
;     this band is a list of byte-lists held in memory. Nothing is written to a file, nothing
;     crosses a process boundary, nothing is timed. What is proven is the DECISION PROCEDURE over
;     a transcript, not the delivery of one. Wiring this to form-stdlib/channel.fk's file-backed
;     CHANNEL-V0 is a later stone and is not attempted here.
;   * NOT that order-independence holds for INCONSISTENT transcripts in the sense of yielding an
;     ack value. It holds in the sense of yielding the SAME answer — CONFLICT — from every
;     ordering. Claim 256 constructs exactly the transcript that should have broken the property
;     (snugcause) and shows the property survives only because the resolver declines. A resolver
;     with a last-one-wins rule would return 2 from one ordering of that transcript and 0 from
;     another; the band asserts the two conflicting tags DIFFER, so that alternative is falsified
;     and not merely disliked.
;   * NOT all orderings. Six are tested, named one by one in claim 128. 4 frames admit 24
;     permutations; 6 of them are exercised, plus one 6-frame duplicate-bearing arrangement. The
;     absorption rules the resolver uses are commutative and idempotent by inspection, which is
;     the reason to expect the other 18 to agree — but they were not run, and this sentence is the
;     honest edge of the claim.
;   * NOT a collision claim about sha256. Two different bodies are shown to have different digests
;     for the specific bodies used here. Nothing here bounds the probability of a collision.
;   * NOT the parser defect's cure. fkwu still answers 3 for a truncated `(do (add 1 2)` today
;     (Stone 18 is healing the parser). This band shows the defect solved ONE LAYER UP: the same
;     truncation, carried as a frame, is decidably incomplete before any parser sees it.
;   * NOT the agent-liveness wiring. Claim 2048 proves the SHAPE that answers "did that agent
;     finish or die?". Nothing in this repo is wired to it. The receipt names how it would apply.
;   * NOT a timing claim. Nothing here is measured in seconds.
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;
;   bit    1  IDENTITY IS CONTENT (axioms/core-axioms.form:51). The same body twice has the same
;             32-byte digest; a body differing in one byte has a different one; and the body's own
;             content-address constructor agrees — (make_nodeid …) over the digest gives node_eq 1
;             for the same composition and 0 for a changed one. The wire digest and the kernel's
;             node identity are the same judgement.
;   bit    2  THE FRAME ROUND-TRIPS. A framed body is complete, its length is 38 + |body|, the body
;             comes back out byte for byte, and the digest the frame DECLARES is the digest of the
;             body it carries — the number both ends compute independently.
;   bit    4  A CUT IS ARITHMETIC. Every one of the 41 proper prefixes of a real frame is refused,
;             none reads complete, and each refusal names WHICH failure it is. Then the sharp case:
;             `(do (add 1 2))` framed and cut to the length of `(do (add 1 2)` answers SHORT-BODY,
;             while `(do (add 1 2)` framed on its own answers COMPLETE with a DIFFERENT digest. The
;             truncated message is not the shorter message, even though its bytes are a prefix of
;             the longer one and parse cleanly.
;   bit    8  CORRUPTION IS NOT LENGTH. One body byte flipped with the length intact answers
;             DIGEST-MISMATCH, not SHORT-BODY; one declared-digest byte flipped answers the same.
;             A right-sized wrong message is still not a message.
;   bit   16  THE STONE — `nothing` SENT vs NO ACK AT ALL. The identical query against two
;             transcripts answers 0 and -1. dc-answered? answers 1 and 0. The ABSENT code is
;             disjoint from all four of axiom-5's ack values, so the confusion this protocol exists
;             to end is not merely unlikely, it is unrepresentable.
;   bit   32  EXACTLY FOUR ACK VALUES (axioms/core-axioms.form:64). nothing / 0 / 1 / node resolve
;             to 0 / 1 / 2 / 3, all distinct, and the node ack carries back the node digest it
;             names, recoverable byte for byte.
;   bit   64  BIDIRECTIONAL BY CONSTRUCTION. A offers and B acks; B offers and A acks; both live on
;             one transcript and both are resolved by the SAME function with NO direction argument,
;             because the query key is a digest and a digest has no sender. Either end may be the
;             asker.
;   bit  128  ORDER-FREE OVER SIX NAMED ORDERINGS: as-sent; fully reversed; every-ack-before-every
;             -offer; rotated by two; a fixed shuffle; and a duplicate-bearing arrangement where two
;             frames each appear twice. All three queries — an offer acked `one`, an offer acked
;             `nothing`, and an offer never mentioned — give identical answers in all six.
;   bit  256  SNUGCAUSE — THE ORDERING BUILT TO BREAK IT. Two valid acks naming one digest with
;             DIFFERENT values. Both orderings answer CONFLICT (-2); a last-one-wins resolver would
;             have answered 2 and 0, and the band asserts those two tags differ so that alternative
;             is falsified. Meanwhile a DUPLICATE ack carrying the SAME value does not conflict —
;             absorbed, because the same composition is the same cell.
;   bit  512  ABSENCE IS STRUCTURAL IN BOTH DIRECTIONS (edgedrop / zerobirth). The empty transcript
;             answers -1 and never 0. An ack whose OFFER is absent still resolves — identity is
;             content, not position (axioms/core-axioms.form:57,
;             reversibility-of-the-referenced). An offer with no ack resolves ABSENT while
;             dc-has-offer answers 1: two independent questions, neither implying the other.
;   bit 1024  BREACH IS OBSERVABLE (axioms/core-axioms.form:59). A byte run that never passed
;             through the frame header — and which is byte-for-byte a well-formed ack BODY, so a
;             lenient scanner would have taken it — answers NOT-A-FRAME. On a transcript carrying
;             it, breach-count is 1, incomplete-count is 1, and the valid ack beside it still
;             resolves correctly. The breach is counted, not skipped, and it does not poison the
;             answer.
;   bit 2048  HUSHEND — A CLOSE CARRIES ITS EVIDENCE. Closed, stopped, and cut are 3, -6 and -7.
;             The close names the digest it closed on and its reason; `done` and `handover` are
;             different reasons — Urs: "going offline and being handed over are clear". A
;             transcript that did not close reports reason -1, so a missing reason cannot read as
;             reason 0.

(do
    ; ---- helpers ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    ; the bytes of `(do (add 1 2))` — carried as ints, never as a string (wraithcarry, 864)
    (defn dcb-prog-whole ()
      (list 40 100 111 32 40 97 100 100 32 49 32 50 41 41))
    ; the bytes of `(do (add 1 2)` — a strict PREFIX of the above, and a program fkwu accepts
    (defn dcb-prog-cut ()
      (list 40 100 111 32 40 97 100 100 32 49 32 50 41))

    (defn dcb-p1 () (list 111 110 101))          ; "one"
    (defn dcb-p2 () (list 116 119 111))          ; "two"
    (defn dcb-p3 () (list 116 101 110))          ; "ten" — offered by nobody in most transcripts

    ; walk every proper prefix of `f` and count how many read COMPLETE. Must be 0.
    (defn dcb-cut-complete-count (f n acc)
      (if (ge n (len f)) acc
        (dcb-cut-complete-count f (add n 1)
          (add acc (dc-frame-complete? (dc-cut f n))))))

    ; walk every proper prefix and count how many carry a NAMED refusal (a negative state).
    (defn dcb-cut-named-count (f n acc)
      (if (ge n (len f)) acc
        (dcb-cut-named-count f (add n 1)
          (add acc (if (lt (dc-frame-state (dc-cut f n)) 0) 1 0)))))

    ; replace byte i of xs with v
    (defn dcb-poke (xs i v)
      (append (take i xs) (cons v (drop (add i 1) xs))))

    ; every ordering must agree with the expected triple, or this is 0
    (defn dcb-triple-ok (t d1 d2 d3 e1 e2 e3)
      (if (eq (dc-resolve t d1) e1)
        (if (eq (dc-resolve t d2) e2)
          (if (eq (dc-resolve t d3) e3) 1 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 1: identity is content — axioms/core-axioms.form:51 --------------------------------
    (let b-a   (dcb-p1))
    (let b-a2  (list 111 110 101))               ; the same composition, built separately
    (let b-b   (list 111 110 102))               ; one byte different
    (let dig-a  (dc-digest b-a))
    (let dig-a2 (dc-digest b-a2))
    (let dig-b  (dc-digest b-b))
    (let cl1 (if (eq (len dig-a) 32)
               (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq dig-a dig-a2) 1)              ; same composition, same cell
                 (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq dig-a dig-b) 0)             ; changed composition, new cell
                   ; and the kernel's OWN content-address constructor renders the same judgement
                   (if (eq (node_eq (dc-nodeid-of-body b-a) (dc-nodeid-of-body b-a2)) 1)
                     (if (eq (node_eq (dc-nodeid-of-body b-a) (dc-nodeid-of-body b-b)) 0)
                         1 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 2: the frame round-trips ----------------------------------------------------------
    (let o1 (dc-offer (dcb-p1)))
    (let d1 (dc-offer-nodeid-bytes o1))
    (let cl2 (if (eq (dc-frame-state o1) (dc-complete))
               (if (eq (len o1) (add 38 4))                       ; 38 header + 1 tag + 3 payload
                 (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq (dc-frame-body o1) (cons 79 (dcb-p1))) 1)
                   ; the digest the frame DECLARES is the digest of the body it carries —
                   ; so both ends compute the same name without being told it
                   (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq d1 (dc-digest (dc-frame-body o1))) 1)
                       2 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 4: a cut is arithmetic ------------------------------------------------------------
    ; every proper prefix of a real frame
    (let cuts-complete (dcb-cut-complete-count o1 0 0))
    (let cuts-named    (dcb-cut-named-count o1 0 0))
    ; the sharp case — the truncation that cost this session real time
    (let f-whole (dc-frame (dcb-prog-whole)))
    (let f-cut   (dc-frame (dcb-prog-cut)))
    ; the stream severed exactly where the shorter valid program ends
    (let severed (dc-cut f-whole (add 38 (len (dcb-prog-cut)))))
    (let cl4 (if (eq cuts-complete 0)                             ; not one prefix reads as a message
               (if (eq cuts-named (len o1))                        ; and every one names its refusal
                 (if (eq (dc-frame-state severed) (dc-short-body)) ; cut mid-write, said so
                   (if (eq (dc-frame-state f-cut) (dc-complete))   ; the shorter text IS a fine message
                     ; …and it is a DIFFERENT one. The truncated whole is not the shorter message,
                     ; though its bytes are a strict prefix and parse cleanly on their own.
                     (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq (dc-frame-declared-digest f-whole)
                                          (dc-frame-declared-digest f-cut)) 0)
                         4 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 8: corruption is not length -------------------------------------------------------
    (let f-badbody (dcb-poke f-whole 40 (add (nth f-whole 40) 1)))     ; a body byte, length intact
    (let f-baddig  (dcb-poke f-whole 10 (add (nth f-whole 10) 1)))     ; a declared-digest byte
    (let cl8 (if (eq (dc-frame-state f-badbody) (dc-digest-mismatch))
               (if (eq (dc-frame-state f-baddig) (dc-digest-mismatch))
                 (if (eq (len f-badbody) (len f-whole))                 ; the same size, still not a message
                     8 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 16: THE STONE — `nothing` sent vs no ack at all -----------------------------------
    (let a-nothing (dc-ack-nothing-frame d1))
    (let t-acked   (list o1 a-nothing))                                ; the receiver said: nothing
    (let t-silent  (list o1))                                          ; the receiver said nothing at all
    (let r-acked   (dc-resolve t-acked d1))
    (let r-silent  (dc-resolve t-silent d1))
    ; The two numbers are pinned as LITERALS, not through the protocol's own constants. A claim
    ; written as (eq r-silent (dc-absent)) would follow the definition wherever it moved — including
    ; onto 0, which is the exact defect this stone exists to end. Mutating dc-absent to 0 must turn
    ; this claim red, and it does.
    (let cl16 (if (eq r-acked 0)                                        ; 0 — an ack WAS sent, of `nothing`
                (if (eq r-silent -1)                                    ; -1 — no ack exists at all
                  (if (eq (eq r-acked r-silent) 0)                      ; and they are not the same number
                    (if (eq (dc-answered? t-acked d1) 1)
                      (if (eq (dc-answered? t-silent d1) 0)
                        ; ABSENT is disjoint from all four of axiom-5's values, so the confusion is
                        ; not unlikely — it is unrepresentable
                        (if (lt (dc-absent) (dc-ack-nothing))
                            16 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 32: exactly four ack values — axioms/core-axioms.form:64 --------------------------
    (let nd (dc-digest (dcb-p2)))                                       ; the node an ack may name
    (let ak-nothing (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-nothing) (empty)))
    (let ak-zero    (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-zero)    (empty)))
    (let ak-one     (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-one)     (empty)))
    (let ak-node    (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-node)    nd))
    (let cl32 (if (eq (dc-resolve (list ak-nothing) d1) 0)
                (if (eq (dc-resolve (list ak-zero) d1) 1)
                  (if (eq (dc-resolve (list ak-one) d1) 2)
                    (if (eq (dc-resolve (list ak-node) d1) 3)
                      ; the node ack carries the node it names back out, byte for byte
                      (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq (dc-ack-node-digest ak-node) nd) 1)
                          32 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 64: bidirectional by construction -------------------------------------------------
    ; A offers p1 and B acks `one`. B offers p2 and A acks `nothing`. One transcript, two directions.
    (let o2 (dc-offer (dcb-p2)))
    (let d2 (dc-offer-nodeid-bytes o2))
    (let a1 (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-one) (empty)))                           ; B -> A
    (let a2 (dc-ack-nothing-frame d2))                                  ; A -> B
    (let t-both (list o1 a1 o2 a2))
    (let cl64 (if (eq (dc-resolve t-both d1) 2)                          ; A asks about its own offer
                (if (eq (dc-resolve t-both d2) 0)                        ; B asks about its own offer
                  ; the SAME function answered both; it takes a digest, and a digest has no sender
                  (if (eq (dc-has-offer t-both d1) 1)
                    (if (eq (dc-has-offer t-both d2) 1)
                        64 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 128: order-free over six NAMED orderings ------------------------------------------
    (let d3 (dc-offer-nodeid-bytes (dc-offer (dcb-p3))))                 ; never mentioned below
    (let ord-sent    (list o1 a1 o2 a2))                                 ; 1. as sent
    (let ord-rev     (list a2 o2 a1 o1))                                 ; 2. fully reversed
    (let ord-acks1st (list a1 a2 o1 o2))                                 ; 3. every reply before every question
    (let ord-rot2    (list o2 a2 o1 a1))                                 ; 4. rotated by two
    (let ord-shuf    (list a1 o2 a2 o1))                                 ; 5. a fixed shuffle
    (let ord-dup     (list o1 a1 a1 o2 a2 o2))                           ; 6. duplicates present
    (let cl128 (if (eq (dcb-triple-ok ord-sent    d1 d2 d3 2 0 -1) 1)
                 (if (eq (dcb-triple-ok ord-rev     d1 d2 d3 2 0 -1) 1)
                   (if (eq (dcb-triple-ok ord-acks1st d1 d2 d3 2 0 -1) 1)
                     (if (eq (dcb-triple-ok ord-rot2    d1 d2 d3 2 0 -1) 1)
                       (if (eq (dcb-triple-ok ord-shuf    d1 d2 d3 2 0 -1) 1)
                         (if (eq (dcb-triple-ok ord-dup     d1 d2 d3 2 0 -1) 1)
                             128 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 256: SNUGCAUSE — the ordering built to break it ------------------------------------
    ; Two valid acks naming ONE digest with DIFFERENT values. This is the only transcript on which
    ; position could possibly matter, so it is the one to construct.
    (let ak-x (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-one) (empty)))                          ; value 2
    (let ak-y (dc-ack d1 (dc-ack-nothing) (empty)))                      ; value 0
    (let conf-fwd (dc-resolve (list o1 ak-x ak-y) d1))
    (let conf-rev (dc-resolve (list o1 ak-y ak-x) d1))
    (let cl256 (if (eq conf-fwd (dc-conflict))
                 (if (eq conf-rev (dc-conflict))
                   ; a last-one-wins resolver would have answered 2 here and 0 there — the two tags
                   ; DIFFER, so that alternative is falsified rather than merely disliked
                   (if (eq (eq (dc-ack-value-tag ak-x) (dc-ack-value-tag ak-y)) 0)
                     ; and a duplicate carrying the SAME value does not conflict: absorbed, because
                     ; the same composition is the same cell
                     (if (eq (dc-resolve (list o1 ak-x ak-x) d1) 2)
                       (if (eq (dc-resolve (list ak-x o1 ak-x) d1) 2)
                           256 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 512: absence is structural in both directions -------------------------------------
    (let t-empty    (empty))
    (let t-ack-only (list a1))                                           ; the ack, its offer absent
    (let t-off-only (list o1))                                           ; the offer, no ack
    ; literals again, for the same reason as claim 16 — the empty transcript must answer -1, and
    ; "never 0" has to be a claim about the number, not about a name that could be redefined to 0
    (let cl512 (if (eq (dc-resolve t-empty d1) -1)                        ; never 0 (zerobirth)
                 (if (eq (dc-resolve t-empty d2) -1)
                   ; reversibility-of-the-referenced (axioms/core-axioms.form:57): the ack resolves
                   ; even though the offer it names is nowhere on this transcript
                   (if (eq (dc-resolve t-ack-only d1) 2)
                     (if (eq (dc-has-offer t-ack-only d1) 0)              ; the offer really is absent
                       ; two independent questions: "was it offered here?" and "was it acked?"
                       (if (eq (dc-resolve t-off-only d1) -1)
                         (if (eq (dc-has-offer t-off-only d1) 1)
                             512 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 1024: breach is observable — axioms/core-axioms.form:59 ---------------------------
    ; A byte run that never passed through the frame header. It is byte-for-byte a well-formed ack
    ; BODY, so a lenient scanner would have taken it as an ack of `one` for d1.
    (let breach (append (list (dc-tag-ack) (dc-ack-one)) d1))
    (let t-breach (list o1 breach a2 o2))
    (let cl1024 (if (eq (dc-frame-state breach) (dc-not-a-frame))
                  (if (eq (dc-breach-count t-breach) 1)                   ; counted, not skipped
                    (if (eq (dc-incomplete-count t-breach) 1)
                      ; and it did NOT become an ack: d1 has no ack on this transcript
                      (if (eq (dc-resolve t-breach d1) -1)
                        ; while the frame that DID cross the interface still answers
                        (if (eq (dc-resolve t-breach d2) 0)
                            1024 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; ---- claim 2048: HUSHEND — a close carries its evidence --------------------------------------
    (let t-closed   (list o1 a1 (dc-close (dc-close-done) d1)))
    (let t-handover (list o1 a1 (dc-close (dc-close-handover) d1)))
    (let t-stopped  (list o1 a1))
    (let t-cut      (list o1 (dc-cut a1 (sub (len a1) 3))))
    (let cl2048 (if (eq (dc-transcript-end t-closed) (dc-end-closed))
                  (if (eq (dc-transcript-end t-stopped) (dc-end-stopped))
                    (if (eq (dc-transcript-end t-cut) (dc-end-cut))
                      ; the close names WHY — and going offline done is not going offline handed over
                      (if (eq (dc-close-evidence t-closed) (dc-close-done))
                        (if (eq (dc-close-evidence t-handover) (dc-close-handover))
                          ; a transcript that did not close reports -1, so a missing reason can
                          ; never read as reason 0
                          (if (eq (dc-close-evidence t-stopped) -1)
                            (if (eq (dc-close-evidence t-cut) -1)
                              ; and the close names the digest it closed ON
                              (if (eq (dc-bytes-eq (dc-close-last (dc-last t-closed)) d1) 1)
                                  2048 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    (add cl1 (add cl2 (add cl4 (add cl8 (add cl16 (add cl32 (add cl64 (add cl128
      (add cl256 (add cl512 (add cl1024 cl2048)))))))))))
)
